Class DefaultBizRulesPlugin

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.bizrules.DefaultBizRulesPlugin
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin, IBizRulesPlugin, java.rmi.Remote

    public class DefaultBizRulesPlugin
extends java.lang.Object
implements IBizRulesPlugin
    Default implementation of the business rules plugin. Customers can override just the methods they use below in order to accept incremental upgrades to the business rules framework.

      • getWhiteListedMethods

        public java.util.Map<IMethodReference,java.lang.String> getWhiteListedMethods()
        Description copied from interface: IBizRulesPlugin
        Provides a list of white-listed methods. These methods will be shown in the auto-completion suggestions. Care must be taken to only expose methods that do not change the state of the system.
        For each method, please provide an optional description to be displayed in Context Help.
        This list can be used to override the default behavior.
        If a method is both white- and black-listed (e.g. through inheritance), it is visible.
        If not specified in either list, the default behavior is for methods on entities to be hidden and methods on other types are visible.
        Specified by:
        getWhiteListedMethods in interface IBizRulesPlugin

      • getBlackListedMethods

        public java.util.Set<IMethodReference> getBlackListedMethods()
        Description copied from interface: IBizRulesPlugin
        Provides a list of black-listed methods. These methods should not be shown in the auto-completion suggestions.
        This list can be used to override the default behavior.
        If a method is both white- and black-listed (e.g. through inheritance), it is visible.
        If not specified in either list, the default behavior is for methods on entities to be hidden and methods on other types are visible.
        Specified by:
        getBlackListedMethods in interface IBizRulesPlugin
